Privacy Policy

Nacos we operates the mobile application Nacos App. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use the App.


1. Information We Collect

We collect the following types of information:

User-Provided Information:

When users create an account or upload content, we collect information such as email address, department, and any PDFs or materials uploaded by the user.


Device & App Usage Information:

We may collect non-personal information such as device model, OS version, and usage statistics to help improve the app’s performance.


Camera Access:

The App may request camera access for the purpose of scanning or uploading PDF materials. Photos or documents taken through the app are used only for educational uploads and are not stored or shared without your consent.


2. How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information to:

Allow users to upload and access educational materials (e.g., past questions, Post UTME documents),

Improve and personalize your user experience,

Ensure security and prevent misuse,

Display non-personalized ads using AdMob (see “Advertising”).


3. Advertising

We use Google AdMob to serve ads in the app. AdMob may collect certain data (e.g., device info, app usage) to show ads.
We do not use personalized advertising targeting based on sensitive user data.

For more info on how Google uses data, visit:
https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites


4. Sharing Your Information

We do not sell or share your personal data with third parties except:

To comply with legal obligations,

To provide services (e.g., hosting or analytics partners) under strict confidentiality agreements.


5. Security

We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. However, no method of transmission over the internet or method of storage is 100% secure.


6. Children’s Privacy

This app is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we learn that a child has provided us with personal information, we will delete it immediately.



7. Your Rights and Choices

You can access, update, or delete your account at any time through the app.

You can revoke camera or storage permissions from your device settings.

8. Content Moderation and User Management

To maintain a safe and appropriate environment:

The app admin has the right to delete any uploaded material that violates app rules (e.g., inappropriate content, spam, or irrelevant files).

The admin can also ban or remove users who engage in behavior that violates the app’s terms, including abuse, spamming, or uploading prohibited content.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. You will be notified of any major changes by an in-app notification or by posting the new policy on this page.

Last updated: 9/7/2025

